<topic id="schematron-resource-hierarchy-view">
  <title>Schematron Resource Hierarchy/Dependencies View</title>
  <prolog>
    <metadata>
      <keywords>
        <indexterm>Schematron Schemas<indexterm>Resource Hierarchy/Dependencies
          view</indexterm></indexterm>
      </keywords>
    </metadata>
  </prolog>
  <body>
    <p>The <uicontrol>Resource Hierarchy/Dependencies</uicontrol> view displays the hierarchy or
      dependencies for resources included in a Schematron schema. <ph
        conkeyref="reusables-user-guide/reopen-view"/></p>
    <p>If you want to see the hierarchy of a schema, select the desired schema in the <xref
        href="using-the-project-view.dita#using-the-project-view"><uicontrol
          product="developer editor">Project</uicontrol><uicontrol
          product="developerEclipse editorEclipse">Project Explorer</uicontrol> view</xref> and choose
        <uicontrol product="developer editor">Resource Hierarchy</uicontrol><uicontrol
        product="developerEclipse editorEclipse">Show Resource Hierarchy</uicontrol> from the
      contextual menu.</p>
    <p>
      <fig>
        <title>Resource Hierarchy</title>
        <image href="../img/sa_schematron_hierarchy.png" placement="inline"/>
      </fig>
    </p>
    <p>If you want to see the dependencies of a schema, select the desired schema in the <xref
        href="using-the-project-view.dita#using-the-project-view"><uicontrol
          product="developer editor">Project</uicontrol><uicontrol
          product="developerEclipse editorEclipse">Project Explorer</uicontrol> view</xref> and choose
        <uicontrol product="developer editor">Resource Dependencies</uicontrol><uicontrol
        product="developerEclipse editorEclipse">Show Resource Dependencies</uicontrol> from the
      contextual menu.</p>
    <p>
      <fig>
        <title>Resource Dependencies</title>
        <image href="../img/sa_schematron_dependencies.png" placement="inline"/>
      </fig>
    </p>
    <p conkeyref="reusables-editing-documents/hierarchy-dependencies-toolbar-actions"/>
    <p conkeyref="reusables-editing-documents/contextual-menu"/>
    <p>
      <note>The <uicontrol>Move resource</uicontrol> or <uicontrol>Rename resource</uicontrol>
        actions give you the option to <xref
          href="move-rename-schematron-resources.dita#move-rename-schematron-resources"
          >update the references to the resource</xref>.</note>
    </p>
  </body>
</topic>
